<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="541" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1585,2008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[330,495,1622,1648]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref6002" refString="Friese, H. (1899 a) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese (1899a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on two females from 
<collectingCountry box="[1091,1159,1622,1648]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(“ 
<collectingRegion box="[1188,1244,1622,1648]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Para</collectingRegion>
” and “Brasilia”) housed at 
<collectionCode box="[270,343,1658,1684]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">NMW</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[355,583,1658,1684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[440,492,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the type series was housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1119,1182,1658,1684]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
, but no primary types were found in either of those institutions. In the 
<collectionCode box="[686,772,1694,1720]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">HNHM</collectionCode>
I found two females, one labeled “Brasilia” and “669 236”, and another one with similar labels, but also containing an original Friese identification label. This latter specimen is here designated 
<typeStatus box="[368,474,1766,1792]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The female has the following data label: Brasilia [printed]\ [light greenish square] 74. [handwritten]\ [black-rimmed] 669. 235 [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Vivallo, 2019" authorityName="Vivallo" authorityYear="2019" box="[824,979,1802,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[824,979,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Centris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[987,1048,1802,1828]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<specimenCount box="[1057,1078,1802,1828]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
[handwritten] det. 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[1296,1436,1802,1828]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="427 - 431" refId="ref5980" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">Friese, 1898</bibRefCitation>
[printed].According to the accession book at 
<collectionCode box="[652,738,1838,1864]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">HNHM</collectionCode>
these specimens were obtained as exchange materials and gifts by Mocsáry during his trip to 
<collectingCountry box="[484,588,1874,1900]" name="Germany" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Germany</collectingCountry>
in 1883. The depository and the current condition of the 
<typeStatus box="[1224,1375,1874,1900]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">paralectotype</typeStatus>
from Pará is unknown.
</paragraph>
